## ADR status

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `Proposed` | Agent draft |
| `Under Review` | Awaiting first acceptance |
| `Accepted` | Decision in force |
| `Reopened` | Was `Accepted`; user reopened with justification |
| `Rejected` | Not adopted |
| `Superseded` | Replaced by another ADR |
| `Deprecated` | Historical only |

## Manual ADR acceptance

| Status | Who sets |
|--------|----------|
| `Proposed`, `Under Review` | Agent or user during elaboration |
| **`Accepted`**, **`Rejected`**, **`Superseded`**, **`Reopened`** | **User only** — explicit chat message |

**Agent must:** draft to `Proposed`; **stop** and ask for acceptance; update to `Accepted` only after user phrase ("Aceito o ADR-NNNN").

**Forbidden:** agent marks `Accepted` on creation; edits `Accepted` body without reopen.

## Reopening an ADR

1. User declares reopen **with justification**.
2. Agent sets **`Reopened`**; Changelog `reopened`.
3. Agent edits body; preserves Changelog history.
4. **Stop**; request new acceptance.
5. After acceptance: `Accepted`; impact review on features and ARCHITECTURE.md.

**Prefer `Superseded` + new ADR** for fundamental scope changes.

## Changelog (every ADR)

```markdown
## Changelog

| Data | Evento | Detalhe |
|------|--------|---------|
| YYYY-MM-DD | proposed | Rascunho inicial. |
| YYYY-MM-DD | accepted | Aceite manual do usuário. |
```

## When to create ADR (phase 2)

| Situation | Action |
|----------|--------|
| Stack, packages, cross-context integration, security transversal | **New ADR** — `Proposed` |
| **AQ*n*** with impact beyond one feature | **New ADR** or edit non-Accepted ADR |
| Single endpoint/template/table for this feature only | Feature **Architecture** section |
| Invalidates Accepted ADR (large change) | New ADR; previous → `Superseded` |

